        "subject": "physics",
        "topic": "Kinematics",
        "question_text": "A car starts from rest and accelerates uniformly at 2 m/s² for 5 seconds. What is the distance travelled by the car?",
        "options": { "A": "25 m", "B": "50 m", "C": "10 m", "D": "100 m" },
        "correct_option": "A",
        "explanation": "The correct option is A because s = (1/2)at². With u=0, a=2 m/s², t=5s → s=25m. Option B wrongly assumes initial velocity. Option C ignores the square of time. Option D forgets the 1/2 factor.",
        "extra": { "difficulty": "medium" },
        "student_answer": "A"
      },
      {
